<div class='external-container main-container'>
  <div class='jumbotron'>
    <h1>London Live Traffic Disruptions</h1>
    <p>A Rails application which consumes the feed at a configurable interval and stores the data in a local model. In particular it consumes the TFL (Transport for London) live traffic disruptions feed called TIMS which can be found at <a href="http://data.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/syndication/feeds/tims_feed.xml">Live Traffic Disruptions - TIMS</a>.</p>
    <p>Currently there are <%= @disruptions.count %> active disruptions.</p>
    <div id="map" data-markers=<%= raw @markers.to_json %>></div>
  </div>
</div>

<% content_for :extra_header_tags do %>
  <script src="//maps.google.com/maps/api/js?v=3.13&sensor=false&libraries=geometry" type="text/javascript"></script>
  <script src='//google-maps-utility-library-v3.googlecode.com/svn/tags/markerclustererplus/2.0.14/src/markerclusterer_packed.js' type='text/javascript'></script>
<% end %>